<?xml version="1.0"?>
<tool id="edu.tamu.cpt.fasta.simpleprimer" name="Simple Primer Generator" version="1.0">
  <description/>
  <version_command>python simple_primer.py --version</version_command>
  <stdio>
    <exit_code level="fatal" range="1:"/>
  </stdio>
  <command interpreter="python">simple_primer.py
${fasta_file}
--end_overlap ${end_overlap}
> $output
</command>
  <inputs>
    <param label="Fasta file" name="fasta_file" type="data" format="fasta"/>
    <param label="End overlap" name="end_overlap" type="integer" value="500"/>
  </inputs>
  <outputs>
    <data format="fasta" name="output">
    </data>
  </outputs>
  <help>Simple Primer Tool
==================

For the example contig:

::

    &gt;test
    aaaaaNNNNNNNNNNNNccccc

Requesting a primer with a 5 base end overlap, you would get

::

    &gt;test
    ccccc[ccc]aaaaa
</help>
  <tests/>
</tool>
